    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> salmon fillet[s] </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 8-9 min, turning once halfway, or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked through when it's opaque and flakes easily</p>",
